}
```

### Explanation

- **`shouldFetchNewLocation`**: This pure function takes the last `SpotNote` and returns `true` if a new location needs to be fetched (either because there is no last note or the last note is older than 5 minutes). Otherwise, it returns `false`.
- **`fetchLocationIfNeeded`**: Another pure function that decides whether to call `locationManger.getLocation()` based on the `shouldFetch` flag. If `shouldFetch` is `false`, it simply returns the last known location. This function assumes that `lastLocation` is not null when `shouldFetch` is `false`.
- **`getNewLocationOrSkip`**: This is the main function that uses the above two functions to decide and fetch the location. It maintains clarity by separating decision logic (`shouldFetchNewLocation`) from action logic (`fetchLocationIfNeeded`).

